In a stock ordering system which of these is the odd one out?
The system should help the company manage its stock levels.
The system must be able to order a given stock item.
The system should be able to display stock levels.
Stock items should be displayed with a picture.
Correct. This is a very general requirement, where as the rest are more fine grain requirements.



The odd one out is The system should help the company manage its stock levels. because it is  a very general requirement, where as the rest are more fine grain requirements.
